Scientific Animations Without Borders (SAWBO) has three animations available in a range of languages that cover ways to combat COVID-19 and stop the spread of germs and disease. SAWBO recently has released a new animation, Protecting Yourself from Coronavirus. This animation addresses best practices to protect against COVID-19 through recommended preventative measures. This animation is available in 15 languages, with more added daily. The World Health Organization lists handwashing as one of the best ways to prevent the spread of germs and diseases. Another SAWBO animation, How to Wash Your Hands, is available in 19 languages. Preventing Sickness gives a basic overview of how diseases and germs transmit from person to person and how to minimize those transmissions. It is available in 11 languages including Chinese, French, Portuguese, and Spanish. All three of these animations are available to view, download, and distribute for free. See below for more information. We encourage you to share these videos across borders and cultures. If you are interested in translating any of these animations into your local language for greater distribution and reach, please email us at contact@sawbo-animations.org (link sends e-mail)  COVID-19 has spread around most parts of the world. This animation addresses best practices to protect against coronavirus through recommended preventative measures. Currently available in 15 languages below. 1) Bamanankan (Mali) YouTube link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lc9FRjufoLM&feature=emb_logo Video Library: https://sawbo-animations.org/866 2) Malagasy (Madagascar) YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S1_T7sIvvY0&feature=emb_logo Video Library: https://sawbo-animations.org/870 3) Zulu (South Africa) YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oh0P7oxp8V4&feature=emb_logo Video Library: https://sawbo-animations.org/872 4) Portuguese (Mozambique) YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-uXZqF8eIRc&feature=emb_logo Video Library: https://saw